revisions.rev:
The [[Devil May Cry|''Devil May Cry'' series]] has seen the release of seven separate soundtracks.
== Pre-Release worries ==
Initially, Capcom was very reluctant to release an officially sanctioned [[video game music|soundtrack]] for the ''Devil May Cry'' series, due to worries that the products would sell poorly. As a means of testing the market, Capcom decided to ask for pre-release sales.<ref>{{cite web| last = Niizumi| first = Hirohiko |title = Capcom considers Devil May Cry soundtrack|date = 2004-08-10|url=http://www.gamespot.com/ps2/action/devilmaycry2/news.html?sid=6104508|accessdate = 2007-03-20}}</ref>
After the pre-release sales were met, the ''[[Devil May Cry (video game)|Devil May Cry]]'' and ''[[Devil May Cry 2]]'' soundtracks were released to the public on October 15, 2004.
Both were released as separate 2-disc sets, with Masami Ueda, Misao Senbongi, and Masato Koda credited as [[music producer|producers]] for the ''Devil May Cry'' soundtrack and Masato Koda, [[Tetsuya Shibata]] and Satoshi Ise credited as producers for the ''Devil May Cry 2'' soundtrack.<ref>{{cite web| title= Amazon.com listing for DMC OST| url= http://www.amazon.com/dp/B000BCN23E| accessdate = 2007-03-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| title = Amazon.com Listing for DMC2 OST| url= http://www.amazon.com/dp/B000CBXDTC | accessdate = 2007-03-20}}</ref>
